CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776477807
OL,3,CFormer BBC DJ and Live Aid presenter
OL,4,CAndy Kershaw dies aged 66
OL,6,FKershaw started his career at the BBC
OL,7,Fin 1984 as the host of its rock music
OL,8,Fshow Old Grey Whistle Test, and later
OL,9,Fco-presented the corporation's
OL,10,Ftelevision coverage of Live Aid.
OL,12,FThe DJ joined Radio 1 as a successor
OL,13,Fto the late John Peel, and became
OL,14,Fknown for his eclectic taste in music,
OL,15,Foften featuring non-mainstream sounds
OL,16,Fon his weekly programme.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
